By Joshua Oladipo Osogbo – The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) says it has certified 1,461 vehicles to be used by the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) for election Duty in Osun. The Sector Commander, Mr Peter Oke, disclosed this in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Thursday in Osogbo. Oke said “The certification which started on February 5 across the
country with Osun not exceptional would be completed before the conduct
of the general elections. “We received about 1,461 vehicles to be certified by INEC but as I speak we have certified about 800 vehicles and left with 661. “I believe before the end of today (Thursday), all vehicles to be
used for the elections in Osun would have been certified and ready for
the expected assignment,” he said. According to him, the purpose of the certification is to allow easy
transportation of election sensitive materials to their locations
without hitches. “We don’t want a situation where vehicles carrying election materials
would breakdown on highway, paving way for unlawful access to such
sensitive materials. “Also, we don’t want any delay in conveying this sensitive materials
to their expected locations with the help of the lead agencies “Police ”
and the electoral umpire (INEC),’’ he said. Oke, however, called for the cooperation of all relevant stakeholders for the successful conduct of the general elections.